{
  "texts": [
    "This kind of automation facilitates the allocation of workers' attention towards jobs of greater significance, fosters innovation, and allows for the allocation of time towards the improvement of their knowledge and skillsets.The name \"Robotic Process Automation\" evokes imagery of physical robots traversing office spaces to carry out operations often conducted by people.",
    "However, in actuality, this word refers to the automation of service jobs that were previously executed by human agents.",
    "Robotic automation refers to the use of specialized technology and approaches to employ a computer or a \"virtualized FTE or robot\" instead of a human being for the purpose of manipulating pre-existing application software.",
    "According to Umble,Haft,and Umble [7], Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) systems function similarly to how individuals now handle transactions or carry out operations, including learning management systems, databases, and claims applications.According to Gomes and Seruca [8], the use of RPA saw significant growth in shared service operations, back offices, and even among entrepreneurship process outsourcing service providers in the year 2016.",
    "The use of RPA is transitioning from experimental initiatives to a more widespread implementation."
  ]
}